{
  "stem": "6773.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They used to go for breakfast and for dinner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] when we started to drink, every night and every morning, we did-- we never-- we never quit until we were evacuated to, to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were taken by train by open cars.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew it the day before, that we were-- we, we will be taken to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that day before, they, they put a ring around the camp so that nobody could escape.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had to abide by going to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the way to Auschwitz, I had some friends which we broke a hole through in the car, the freight car.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they slipped through, but I don't know what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never met them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I've never seen them again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember, but now it's-- in a minute, it's just out of my mind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we considered too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was there with my, my two brothers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I don't think it was that was enough time for all three of us to go through.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then later, we abandoned that and we decided to go with everybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That journey was a whole day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the train, there was-- there was no conditions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't get anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We, we didn't need anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Whoever was smart, took along with them some bread or something to drink.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But most people had nothing with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we came to Auschwitz, we undressed, and we went into Auschwitz without anything on our-- on our body.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We got the numbers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we arrived to Auschwitz, we went to the-- to the bath house.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
